## Grafana Architecture

### Core Components

- **Grafana Server**: Main application server
- **Data Sources**: Connections to Prometheus, Loki, etc.
- **Dashboards**: Visual representations of metrics/logs
- **Panels**: Individual visualizations within dashboards
- **Alerting**: Rule evaluation and notification engine

### Loki Deployment Modes

1. **Standalone** (not recommended for production)
2. **Simple Scalable Deployment (SSD)** - Recommended for most use cases
3. **Microservices Mode** - For large-scale deployments

**CRITICAL**: Run Loki in SSD or microservices mode for optimal performance.

**Source**: [Loki Performance Guide](https://grafana.com/blog/2023/12/28/the-concise-guide-to-loki-how-to-get-the-most-out-of-your-query-performance)

