## Dashboard Best Practices

### General Guidelines

1. **Use template variables** for filtering (reduce duplicate dashboards)
2. **Organize panels logically** (group related metrics)
3. **Set appropriate time ranges** (default to last 6h or 24h)
4. **Use consistent units** (milliseconds, bytes, etc.)
5. **Add descriptions** to panels for clarity
6. **Limit panels per dashboard** (10-15 for performance)

**Source**: [Grafana Dashboard Best Practices](https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/build-dashboards/best-practices/)

### Performance Optimization

1. **Reduce query frequency**: Set refresh intervals appropriately
2. **Use query caching**: Enable when available
3. **Limit time ranges**: Shorter ranges = faster queries
4. **Use downsampling**: For long-term historical data
5. **Avoid wildcard queries**: Be specific with metrics/logs

