## LogQL Performance

### Most Important Optimization (CRITICAL)

**Use precise label selectors** rather than wildcards.

```logql
# ❌ BAD: Wildcard (scans many streams)
{namespace=~".*"}

# ✅ GOOD: Specific selector (scans fewer streams)
{namespace="production", app="api"}
```

**Why**: This is the **#1 most important** performance improvement technique. Reduces log volume searched dramatically.

**Source**: [5 Tips for Loki Performance](https://grafana.com/blog/2023/01/10/watch-5-tips-for-improving-grafana-loki-query-performance)

### Line Filters (Second Most Important)

**Use line filter expressions** to further accelerate queries.

```logql
# ✅ GOOD: Line filter reduces data processing
{namespace="production", app="api"} |= "error"

# ✅ BETTER: Multiple filters
{namespace="production", app="api"} 
  |= "error" 
  != "timeout"
```

**Why**: Line filters reduce data processing after stream selection.

**Source**: [5 Tips for Loki Performance](https://grafana.com/blog/2023/01/10/watch-5-tips-for-improving-grafana-loki-query-performance)

### LogQL Query Optimization

```logql
# ❌ BAD: Too broad, processes millions of logs
{job="varlogs"} |= "error"

# ✅ GOOD: Specific labels + line filter
{job="varlogs", namespace="production", app="api"} 
  |= "error" 
  | json 
  | status_code >= 500

# ✅ BEST: Additional filters and limited time range
{job="varlogs", namespace="production", app="api"} 
  |= "error" 
  | json 
  | status_code >= 500
  | duration > 1s
# Use last 1h time range instead of 24h
```

### Automatic Stream Sharding (CRITICAL)

**Enable automatic stream sharding** for better query parallelization.

**Note**: Currently not enabled by default (as of 2026).

**Configuration**:
```yaml
# loki-config.yaml
ingester:
  max_chunk_age: 2h
  chunk_idle_period: 1h
  chunk_target_size: 1536000
  chunk_encoding: snappy
  # Enable stream sharding
  max_streams_per_user: 0  # Unlimited
  stream_sharding:
    enabled: true
```

**Source**: [Loki Performance Guide](https://grafana.com/blog/2023/12/28/the-concise-guide-to-loki-how-to-get-the-most-out-of-your-query-performance)

### Baseline Best Practices

1. **Keep Loki upgraded** to latest release (performance improvements)
2. **Run in SSD or microservices mode** (not standalone)
3. **Manage labels carefully** (avoid high cardinality)
4. **Use retention policies** (delete old logs)
5. **Enable query caching** (faster repeated queries)

**Source**: [Loki Performance Guide](https://grafana.com/blog/2023/12/28/the-concise-guide-to-loki-how-to-get-the-most-out-of-your-query-performance)

