## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 1: Wildcard Label Selectors

```logql
# ❌ BAD: Scans all streams
{namespace=~".*", app=~".*"}

# ✅ GOOD: Specific selectors
{namespace="production", app="api"}
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 2: No Line Filters

```logql
# ❌ BAD: Processes all logs
{namespace="production"} | json

# ✅ GOOD: Filter first
{namespace="production"} |= "error" | json
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 3: Too Many Panels

```
❌ BAD: 50 panels on one dashboard (slow load)
✅ GOOD: 10-15 panels per dashboard
✅ BETTER: Multiple focused dashboards
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 4: Short Time Windows

```promql
# ❌ BAD: Too noisy (30s window)
rate(http_requests_total[30s])

# ✅ GOOD: Smoothed (5m window)
rate(http_requests_total[5m])
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 5: No Alert Annotations

```yaml
# ❌ BAD: No context
- alert: HighCPU
  expr: cpu > 80

# ✅ GOOD: With context
- alert: HighCPU
  expr: cpu > 80
  annotations:
    summary: "CPU usage high on {{ $labels.instance }}"
    runbook_url: "https://wiki/runbooks/high-cpu"
```

